================================================================================

GlanceTerm modifications on top of Tabby:

1. tabby-core — added a `SidebarProvider` extension point so plugins can
   contribute a left-hand panel rendered alongside the tab area.

     - new:      tabby-core/src/api/sidebarProvider.ts
     - new:      tabby-core/src/services/sidebar.service.ts
     - modified: tabby-core/src/components/appRoot.component.{ts,pug,scss}

2. tabby-plugin-ai-sidebar — new plugin (not present in upstream Tabby) that
   ships the AI agent status sidebar. Covers:

     - per-tab hook installation for supported AI tools (Claude Code today;
       Codex / Gemini / aider planned)
     - real-time status tracking (working / idle / done / needs_permission)
       via filesystem-watched hook events
     - opt-in auto-approve of Claude permission prompts, with on-disk audit
       log at ~/.glanceterm/auto-approve.log
     - screenshot capture with per-agent paste adapters
     - split-shell launcher matching the active tab's working directory

3. Branding rename (Tabby → GlanceTerm) in user-facing strings, app
   metadata, and packaging config. The npm package names of upstream
   tabby-* modules are kept unchanged so the plugin ecosystem stays
   source-compatible.

For the authoritative diff, see the git history relative to the merge base
with https://github.com/Eugeny/tabby at tag v1.0.234.
